# Google Maps API Integration Rules

## Smart API Detection
- Use smart API detection with modern APIs when available
- Fallback to legacy APIs when needed
- Prefer `google.maps.places.Place.searchByText()` over `PlacesService.nearbySearch()`
- Use `googlePlacesService` abstraction layer for all Google Places operations

## API Support
- Support both modern and legacy APIs:
  - **Modern**: Place, PlaceAutocompleteElement, AutocompleteSuggestion
  - **Legacy**: PlacesService, AutocompleteService
- Ensure graceful degradation
- Avoid deprecation warnings

## Best Practices
- Use modern APIs when available
- Implement proper error handling for API failures
- Cache API responses when appropriate
- Handle rate limiting gracefully
- Use environment variables for API keys
- Never expose API keys in client-side code

## Abstraction Layer
- Use `googlePlacesService` for all Google Places operations
- Implement consistent error handling
- Provide fallback mechanisms
- Abstract API version differences
- Maintain backward compatibility
